Feature A - SCA Dependency Hallucination Defense (Layer 2b):
- Opt-in via allowlist.yml in repo root (absent = skip)
- Scans manifest diffs (requirements.txt, package.json, go.mod, Cargo.toml,
  pyproject.toml) for packages not on the per-language allowlist
- Unverified packages add +3 to verdict score (CAUTION floor), controlled by
  sca.fail_on_unknown config key
- Report: sca.{status, unverified_packages, manifest_files_scanned, allowlist_active}
Feature B - Cyclomatic Complexity Advisory (advisory, no score impact):
- Newly added Python functions with V(G) > threshold (default 15) appear in
  complexity_advisory list in both JSON and markdown reports
- V(G) = 1 + sum(If, For, While, ExceptHandler) + sum(BoolOp.values - 1)
- Only added functions are checked
Infrastructure:
- __version__ = "1.1.0" added to analyze.py
- import ast added (stdlib, no new dependency)
- DEFAULT_CONFIG extended: structural.complexity_threshold, sca section
- PayloadGuardConfig extended: sca field
- _assess_consequence() extended: unverified_dependencies param
Tests: 151 pass, 7 skipped (crypto/tree-sitter env limitations).
